[medium] src/views/system-security-plans/partials/StatementByComponent.vue:36 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
The new guarded watcher uses immediate: false. If this partial is mounted after ssp.uuid and byComponent.componentUuid are already available, which is the normal pattern when the parent gates rendering on ssp.uuid, componentUrl never changes and fetchComponent is never called; because the template is guarded by v-if="component", the by-component row renders nothing.
Suggested fix: Set the watcher to immediate: true while keeping the null URL guard, and add a test for the initial-props-ready case in addition to the delayed-SSP case.
Guidance: In src/views/system-security-plans/partials/StatementByComponent.vue, the watch(componentUrl, ...) currently uses { immediate: false }. Change it to { immediate: true } while keeping the existing if (!url) return guard and useDataApi(..., { immediate: false }) so no request fires until a valid URL exists. This is required for the normal mount path where props.ssp.uuid and props.byComponent.componentUuid are already populated before the watcher is registered. Add a test next to src/views/system-security-plans/partials/__tests__/StatementByComponent.spec.ts for the initial-props-ready case: mount with ssp { uuid: 'ssp-1' } and byComponent { componentUuid: 'component-1' }, then assert execute was called once with /api/oscal/system-security-plans/ssp-1/system-implementation/components/component-1. Keep the existing delayed-SSP test so the guard still proves it avoids undefined URLs.
